@node 1 "What the fuck..."

SnatchDIZ  is  another  FILE_ID.DIZ extractor for the Shell or for use with
any bbs-system.  Features:

 - LHA-, LZX-, ZIP-, DMS-, EXE-, GIF-, TXT-support
 - SnatchDIZ is smaller than 3 KB and faaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaast (1oo% asm)!
 - great code: SnatchDIZ does not produce HITS like WhaDIZ, SpeeDIZ etc.
 - reentrant (can be made resident)
 - good error handling: no problems with empty files or something

-=> Use SnatchDIZ instead of all the other crap floating around!
@endnode
@node 2 "It's easy..."

Usage: SnatchDIZ FILE/A,S=SUPPRESS/S
=====================================

For example:  "SnatchDIZ dh0:down/PPLAY41.LZX S K" will give you

--------------------------------------
Power Player 4.1 Final Omega Version
* Latest Update! *
--------------------------------------

This extracts and shows the file_id.diz and suppresses the credits and the
filetype indicator.

WARNINGS: - SnatchDIZ is cli-only so don't start from Workbench!
@endnode
@node 3 "You got this crap..."

You need:

 - an AMIGA w/Kick 2.04+ (as always).
 - the lha-, lzx- and UNzip-executable placed in your path.
   A working UNzip is included in the SnatchDIZ-archive.

That's it.
@endnode
